# Walkthrough - UI Optimization & Progression Fix

I have implemented the requested UI improvements and fixed the roadblock that prevented proceeding to the next Game Week.

## Critical Fixes & Improvements

### 1. Game Progression Fix
- **[game_screen.dart](file:///Users/amolsehgal/antigravity%20-%20touchline%20tantrum/touchline_tantrum/lib/screens/game_screen.dart)**: Fixed a logic bug where the "processing lock" wasn't being released after match simulations. You can now reliably swipe or click the match result card to proceed to the next week.

### 2. UI Layout Optimization (Reduced Scrolling)
I have compressed the game UI to ensure all key elements fit on standard screens without needing to scroll down:
- **Compressed League Table**: Reduced the vertical height and padding of the league table.
- **Smaller Stat Rings & Manager**: Reduced the size of the stat rings (120 -> 100) and the manager mood box (100 -> 80).
- **Slimmer Action Cards**: Reduced the internal padding of the main decision cards.
- **Tighter Spacing**: Removed unnecessary gaps between the table, stats, and cards.
- **Optimized Action Buttons**: Positioned the swipe buttons more efficiently to reclaim vertical space.

